      "description": "Make the Poached Chicken &amp; Ginger Broth."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring the leftover chicken broth to just below a simmer in a large saucepan. Stir in the fish sauce, salt and sugar, if using. Taste and tweak, it should be savoury, lightly sweet and properly seasoned."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Warm the poached chicken in the broth for a couple of minutes until hot through, then lift it out and shred."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook the noodles following pack instructions. Drain and divide between bowls."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Ladle the hot broth over the noodles, then top each bowl with a portion of shredded chicken."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thinly slice the spring onions and Thai chillies. Pick the coriander and mint leaves. Slice the limes into wedges."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Scatter the spring onions, beansprouts, coriander, mint and chillies over each bowl. Add a wedge of lime and a good squeeze of sriracha to finish."
